lines.text: like a drunk on a vacant street.
silently beset by the hands of time
an aberrant crack as skeleletons yield
while viruses prowl for helpless victims
tell me! tell me where is the love?
just a cause and a cure
is that they call it "god's love".
there's a truth and we all submit.
so tell me! tell me where is the love?
just a cause and a cure
is that they call it "god's love".
i know there's no reason for alarm.
when it comes to pain and harm.
but first you've got to tell me!
tell me where is the love?
just a cause and a cure
is that they call it "god's love".

paragraphs.text: striking at mental apparitions like a drunk on a vacant street. silently beset by the hands of time indelicate in it's fury. an aberrant crack as skeleletons yield to unrelenting gravity. while viruses prowl for helpless victims who succumb rapidl-y. tell me! tell me where is the love? in a careless creation. when there's no "above".
there's no justice just a cause and a cure and a bounty of suffering. it seems we all endure and what i'm frightened of is that they call it "god's love".
well, twisted torment, make-believe. there's a truth and we all submit. "believe my eyes," my brain complies to all that they interpret.

so tell me! tell me where is the love? in a careless creation. when there's no "above". there's no justice just a cause and a cure and a bounty of suffering. it seems we all endure and what i'm frightened of is that they call it "god's love".

i know there's no reason for alarm. but who needs perspective when it comes to pain and harm. we can change our minds; there's a better prize. but first you've got to tell me! tell me where is the love? in a careless creation. when there's no "above".
there's no justice just a cause and a cure and a bounty of suffering. it seems we all endure and what i'm frightened of is that they call it "god's love".
they call it god's love. my pain is god's love.
